(`Task 2/ner/prepare_data.py`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This script generates synthetic training data in JSONL format.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main idea:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(define canonical animals and alias forms;) Tj
T*
(insert them into sentence templates;) Tj
T*
(generate BIO tags \(`B-ANIMAL`, `I-ANIMAL`, `O`\);) Tj
T*
(add negative examples with no animal entity;) Tj
T*
(split into train/validation/test.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important internal pieces:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`ANIMALS`: canonical label to alias list mapping.) Tj
T*
(`TEMPLATES`: single-animal sentence patterns.) Tj
T*
(`MULTI_TEMPLATES`: sentences with two animals.) Tj
T*
(`NEGATIVE_TEMPLATES`: sentences with no entities.) Tj
T*
(`to_bio\(...\)`: converts token spans into BIO labels.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What this file really does architecturally:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(it removes the need for a manually annotated dataset;) Tj
T*
(it makes the NER training fully reproducible;) Tj
T*
(it constrains the problem to a template-based language space.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practical consequence:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(the model can learn the target label format easily,) Tj
T*
(but generalization to more natural and messy user text may be limited.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`Task 2/ner/train.py`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is the NER training entry point.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Responsibilities:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(load JSONL data;) Tj
T*
(convert it into Hugging Face `Dataset` objects;) Tj
T*
(tokenize split tokens with `is_split_into_words=True`;) Tj
T*
(align word-level BIO labels to subword tokens;) Tj
T*
(fine-tune a transformer token-classification model;) Tj
T*
(save both model and tokenizer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key design decisions:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(default base model: `distilbert/distilbert-base-uncased`;) Tj
T*
