(labels are fixed to `["O", "B-ANIMAL", "I-ANIMAL"]`;) Tj
T*
(special tokens and non-leading subtokens receive label `-100`,) Tj
T*
(so they are ignored in the loss.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This file is the most important implementation detail in the NER pipeline, because label) Tj
T*
(alignment is the critical step when moving from word-level annotations to transformer) Tj
T*
(tokenization.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(`Task 2/ner/inference.py`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This file serves as the NER inference layer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Responsibilities:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(load the trained model with Hugging Face `pipeline\(task="token-classification"\)`;) Tj
T*
(aggregate subword predictions using `aggregation_strategy="simple"`;) Tj
T*
(keep only entities with group `ANIMAL`;) Tj
T*
(normalize plural or variant surface forms into canonical labels.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key point:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(the normalization dictionary is not identical to the training aliases.) Tj
T*
(For example, it includes labels like `lion`, `tiger`, `bear`, `fox`, `wolf`,) Tj
T*
(even though the synthetic training data generator focuses on another animal set.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This means inference tries to be broader than the training generator, but the trained) Tj
T*
(model may not reliably support those extra forms unless it generalizes beyond the) Tj
T*
(synthetic data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(NER Data Contract) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Every JSONL row must look like:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
({"tokens": ["There", "is", "a", "cow", "."], "ner_tags": ["O", "O", "O", "B-ANIMAL",) Tj
T*
("O"]}) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This contract is important because both training and label alignment assume a tokenized) Tj
T*
(input rather than raw text with character offsets.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
